physical_examinations.relevant_findings: General: Alert and generally comfortable in bed; Eyes: Anicteric, pupils equally round; ENT: Ears and nose without visible erythema, masses, or trauma; Oropharynx without visible lesion, erythema or exudate; CV: Heart regular, no murmur, no S3, no S4; No JVD; RESP: Lungs clear to auscultation with good air movement bilaterally; Breathing is non-labored; GI: Abdomen soft, non-distended, TTP in RUQ, but otherwise non-tender to palpation; Bowel sounds present; No HSM; Obese; GU: No suprapubic fullness or tenderness to palpation; MSK: Neck supple, moves all extremities, strength grossly full and symmetric bilaterally in all limbs; SKIN: No rashes or ulcerations noted; NEURO: Alert, oriented, face symmetric, gaze conjugate with EOMI, speech fluent, moves all limbs, sensation to light touch grossly intact throughout; PSYCH: pleasant, appropriate affect
